latestPosts.caption:
B.Com degree is your foundation.
But your CAREER is built by what you add ON TOP of it 💼👇

Here’s a premium roadmap of high-paying careers after B.Com — and the skills you must pair them with:

💼 1. Corporate Finance / Investment Banking

🎯 Learn:
	•	Financial modelling, ratios, company analysis
	•	Pitch decks & Excel dashboards

📚 Platforms:
	•	[Coursera] – Financial Markets by Yale
	•	[WallStreetPrep] or [Financial Edge] – Pro-level IB training
	•	[YouTube] – CA Rachana Ranade, Investopedia tutorials

📊 2. Data Analytics / Business Intelligence

🎯 Learn:
	•	Excel (Advanced), SQL, Power BI, Tableau

📚 Platforms:
	•	[Google Data Analytics Certificate] – Coursera
	•	[Microsoft Learn] – Power BI path (free!)
	•	[YouTube] – Krish Naik, Luke Barousse

💡 Tip: Build dashboards using dummy data from [Kaggle]

📢 3. Digital Marketing + Brand Strategy

🎯 Learn:
	•	SEO, Google Ads, Social Media Strategy, Copywriting

📚 Platforms:
	•	[Google SkillShop] – FREE certifications
	•	[Meta Blueprint] – Ads & Instagram strategy
	•	[HubSpot Academy] – Email & Inbound Marketing
	•	[YouTube] – Neil Patel, Marketing Harry

📚 4. CA / ACCA

🎯 Learn:
	•	Accounting, taxation, audit, laws

📚 Prep With:
	•	ICAI (India) – [https://www.icai.org/]
	•	ACCA Global – [https://www.accaglobal.com/]
	•	Classes: Unacademy, Finology, Edu91

🧠 5. Financial Advisory + CFP

🎯 Learn:
	•	Mutual Funds, Retirement Planning, Tax Saving

📚 Platforms:
	•	[NISM Modules] – Mutual Fund Advisor
	•	[CFP India] – cfp.net.in
	•	[Zerodha Varsity] – Free beginner to pro investing guide

💼 6. Freelance Finance Projects / Entrepreneurship

🎯 Learn:
	•	Canva, Proposal Writing, Market Research

📚 Where to Learn:
	•	[Canva Design School] – Free branding courses
	•	[Fiverr Learn] – Freelance-specific modules
	•	[Internshala] – Finance, Business Development projects

💡 Tip: Build LinkedIn + Fiverr profile by 2nd year

🚨 CUET 2025 Answer Key — Wrong Answers? Your Score Is NOT Final Yet.
🎯 Students are panicking… but here’s the truth NOBODY is telling you:

🧾 The provisional answer key is NOT the final say.
It’s just what NTA “thinks” is right — not what’s actually correct.
You have until 20 June to challenge wrong answers.
Then → final answer key → raw score → normalization → your real result.

💬 Scoring low right now?
👉 Don’t panic. Don’t decide your future on an unfinished result.
Competition is low this year. Cutoffs may drop.
And DU is NOT the only good college.

📍 Ambedkar University | IPU | Shiv Nadar | Christ | Ashoka
So many powerful options.
Drop should be the LAST option.
